The paper discusses a neuro-inspired model for network flow control that relies on modifying edge weights in an activity-dependent manner, which is similar to the synaptic plasticity rules observed in the brain. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
